===Etymology===
From German [[Lämmergeier]], from [[Lämmer]] plural of [[Lamm]] ‘lamb’ + [[Geier]] ‘vulture’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈlæməgaɪə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A rare long-winged [[vulture]], ''Gypaetus barbatus'', found in southern Europe, Africa and India.

